author: The Columbus Dispatch
title: Ohio State vs. Penn State | Three points
text:
>> Got a question about Ohio State football? Ask the experts! 
Star of the game The play of quarterback J.T. Barrett indicated a changing of the guard, at least at starter. He ran for 102 yards and two touchdowns, and he passed for two more scores, including a jump-pass TD to Braxton Miller.
>> Click for details on how to win tickets and trips to OSU games from  Dispatch  Reader Rewards 
Turning point When coach Urban Meyer sent Barrett in to quarterback with 3:18 left in the third quarter and the ball at the OSU 25-yard line. That’s not the red zone. Barrett responded by leading the team to a field goal, and then to two more touchdowns — five in all — as the offense blossomed.
>> Get the most out of your Ohio State experience, follow @BuckeyeXtra on Twitter 
Repercussions Based on the scoring blitz in the last 20 minutes, one would think the top-ranked Buckeyes will hold to their No. 1 spot in the polls. Past that, they found a credible offense with Barrett at the controls, and it came against the No.10 defense in the country.
